<div class="help-instructions">
  <h6><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle text-warning me-2"></i>Warning</h6>
  <p>Please be careful with the data that you are uploading. If you are not careful, you could end up with incorrect data and another run is needed.</p>
  <p>Here is a check list of what you need to verify before running the tool:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      If the bid sheet uses ports as origins: you need to make sure that you have added the <b>exact port name</b> to the <a href="/ports">ports</a> page.
    </li>
    <li>
      The rate per mile is correct and it is not accounting for fuel or round trip. Typically this has been set to 1.93.
    </li>
    <li>
      The fuel surcharge is correct. This has been set to 0 for previous runs but it is an option if needed.
    </li>
    <li>
      The accurate miles is set to false. This has been set to false for previous runs but it is an option if needed.
    </li>
    <li>
      The column mapping is correct: there are two columns for destination and origin because some bid sheets may have multiple columns for the destination and origin and some may not. If it doesn't you can leave the second one for each blank
    </li>
    <li>
      The column names need to match the names of the columns in the CSV file.
    </li>
  </ul>
