  <h6><i class="fas fa-upload text-primary me-2"></i>CSV Upload & Processing</h6>
  <p>This tool is designed to help you fill out bids with a lot of columns and should be used carefully to ensure that it is all correct.</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      Prepare your data: open up the excel file and export the sheet that contains the origins and destinations as a <b>CSV file</b>.
    </li>
    <li>
      Fill out rate per mile <b>without fuel</b> -- the distance that is used is round trip so make sure you do not double the price to account for that
    </li>
    <li>
      Fill out the fuel surcharge. -- This can stay as 0 if the bid requires fuel to be excluded.
    </li>
    <li>
      Ensure that you have the correct setting for accurate miles. -- This has been set to false (unchecked) for previous runs but it is an option if needed
    </li>
    <li>
      Upload the CSV file.
    </li>
    <li>
      In the column mapping, you need to set the names of the columns to the names of the columns in the CSV file.
    </li>
    <li>
      Click the "Run" and wait. Please be patient as it can take a while to run since it is calling google's servers.
    </li>
    <li>
      When ready it will show you the results that you can download
    </li>
    <li>
      Copy and paste the results into the excel file.
    </li>
  </ol>
